+++ b/doc/lispref/windows.texi
@@ -5982,6 +5982,28 @@ Window Point
 selected window.
 @end defun

+@defun set-window-extra-cursors window cursors
+Set the display-only extra cursor positions of @var{window} to
+@var{cursors}, a proper list of integer buffer positions or live markers in
+the buffer displayed by @var{window}.  Markers track buffer edits; integers
+do not.  Changing the displayed buffer clears the list.
+
+On graphical displays, visible positions are drawn as filled box cursors by
+the native cursor glyph renderer.  They do not act as point or mark, cause
+scrolling, execute commands, or own the system input, IME, or accessibility
+caret.  Text terminals do not display extra cursors.  Dead markers,
+positions that become inaccessible, and off-screen positions are skipped.
+Extra cursors at exact-window-width line endings that must be represented in
+the fringe are not yet displayed; ordinary end-of-line and horizontally
+scrolled margin positions are supported.
+The return value is @var{cursors}.
+@end defun
+
+@defun window-extra-cursors &optional window
+Return the list installed for @var{window}, which defaults to the selected
+window.
+@end defun
+
 @defun window-cursor-info &optional window
 This function returns information about the cursor of @var{window},
 defaulting to the selected window.
